- daeal with three problem * The complexity of the relationship between net rent and the explanatory variables. * Non-homogeneity of variance of rent. * Skewness in the distribution of the response variable rent.

First approach

  • use linear model

modeling the scale parameter

  • for a gamma distribution if we known the mean and variance we can caculate the scale parameter

data=rent)

introduction to gamlss packages

library(gamlss)
data(film90)
#一周票房與首映票房關係
plot(lborev1~lboopen, data=film90, col="blue", xlab="log opening revenue",
ylab="log extra revenue")

##simple linear model and cubic polynomial

#simple linear model
m0 <- gamlss(lborev1~lboopen, data=film90)
## GAMLSS-RS iteration 1: Global Deviance = 15079.74 
## GAMLSS-RS iteration 2: Global Deviance = 15079.74
plot(lborev1~lboopen, data=film90, col = "lightgray", lty=4)
lines(fitted(m0)~film90$lboopen)

#cubic polynomial model
#poly正交多項式使各項不相干
m0 <- gamlss(lborev1~poly(lboopen,3), data=film90, family=NO)
## GAMLSS-RS iteration 1: Global Deviance = 14518.26 
## GAMLSS-RS iteration 2: Global Deviance = 14518.26
summary(m0)
